my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Loading and discharging to be planned and carried out by a competent person(s); 
b) A stowage plan should be passed to the foreman / stevedores for their reference; 
c) The Master or Chief Officer must be and remain in overall charge of cargo operations; 
d) The loading program must be designed, approved and certified for the vessel; 
e) The loading program must be checked in accordance with the manufacturer's manual and Company MPM system; 
f) Ensure that there is sufficient stability at all times during loading / discharging; 
g) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
h) Ballast operations to be carried out in line with cargo operations; 
i) Particular attention should be made to cargo being loaded / discharged on deck; 
j) Cargo entrances / hatches must be closed and battened down prior to proceeding to sea; 
k) The vessel's draft and stability condition must be assessed prior to proceeding to sea.

a) All crew involved in cargo operations must have the necessary training and understanding; 
b) Loading and discharging to be planned and carried out by a competent person(s); 
c) Ensure that the port / sea mode on the loading program is used correctly for the calculations. 
d) Consult the vessel's stowage plan; 
e) The vessel's allowable stress limits should not be exceeded; 
f) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
g) Ballast operations to be carried out in line with cargo operations; 
h) Ensure that the port / sea mode on the loading program is used correctly for the calculations.

a) Any relevant port information i.e. approach, available depth at the berth, any restriction in draft, must be obtained prior to submitting the stowage plan - Such information should also be included in the passage plan; 
b) The vessel should stay within a safe UKC at all times, as laid out by the Master; 
c) The echo sounder should be powered on if required.
